# Study-I: UAS-based Feature Engineering for BYD disease prediction

## Specific objectives of Study-I:

1.  To compare vegetation indices derived from RGB and Multispectral sensors for predicting BYD disease
2.  To find out the extent to which pixel-level variation predicts severity
3.  To assess height-based pixel filtering from DEMs to isolate disease-susceptible regions

# Study-II: Comparison between models for BYD disease prediction ​

## Specific objectives of Study-II:

1.  To compare between different machine learning models such as random forest, support vector, and deep learning models​
2.  To find out the model that best predicts BYD disease

