## Machine learning models for disease prediction in wheat

[@kumar2022] showed a distinguishable growth in the identification of wheat disease (fungal, bacterial, and viral) using deep learning models in last 7-8 years, among which, ANN was the most widely used DL method, followed by CNN. [@mehra2016] examined the performance of multiple regression (MR) and three deep learning models- artificial neural network (ANN), categorical and regression trees, and random forest (RF) to predict pre-planting risk of SNB in wheat, and found out RF to be the most accurate in predicting the research interest, among all other models used thereby. [@li2022] proposed a method of combining a logistic regression mechanism based model and k-nearest neighbor (KNN) model to predict wheat fusarium head blight. [@liu2024] used eight machine learning models including random forest and support vector, and concluded that three plus kinship (K) method achieved high prediction accuracy. For monitoring powdery mildew disease severity in wheat, [@feng2022] compared three different models and summarized that random forest regression performed best, while support vector regression and partial least square regression performed similarly.

