# Expected Outcomes

The use of different filtered VIs based on spectra, statistics, and height levels will detect BYD disease in a more efficient way, and thus developed models, could be used to distinguish other plant diseases in the future. The research is expected to develop a trained model that will show a comparable accuracy in BYD rating using multispectral imagery than visual rating. It will help breeders for the large-scale selection of BYD resistance in wheat.

\newpage

# Limitations

1.  Since only the temporal window of BYD disease was considered, no visible patches of BYD were observed in the field during the 2024–25 season, so we could not use the images from that year for our analysis.
2.  It was difficult to align UAV flight schedule with the BYD rating date because of challenging environmental condition for a few days, leading to a slight temporal misalignment between images and ground truth values.

